The White House has launched the "Healthy Communities Challenge" to engage communities with high numbers of uninsured individuals. The goal is to help these communities reach the uninsured and assist them in gaining health coverage. At the end of the enrollment period, the Department of Health and Human Services will compare the number of new signups in each community to the estimated number of eligible uninsured individuals at the start of enrollment. The community with the most progress will be visited by President Obama to celebrate their success. Atlanta is one of the 20 communities participating in the challenge. The article also provides information about health insurance coverage in Georgia, including the affordability of plans and the availability of tax credits. It emphasizes the importance of shopping for the lowest-cost plan and highlights the progress made in reducing the uninsured rate in Georgia.